  "prompt": "Will Batman v Superman: Dawn of Justice flop?",
  "response": "As of my knowledge cutoff in October 2023, **\"Batman v Superman: Dawn of Justice\"** was **not a flop** in terms of box office performance, but it received a **mixed response** from both critics and audiences.\n\n### **Box Office Performance**\n- **Worldwide Gross:** Approximately **$873 million**.\n- **Budget:** Estimated around **$250\u2013300 million**.\n  \nThis means the film was financially successful, earning nearly **three times its production budget** globally. Additionally, when considering marketing and other associated costs, it still managed to secure significant earnings.\n\n### **Critical and Audience Reception**\n- **Critical Reviews:** The movie received **mixed to negative reviews** from critics. Common criticisms focused on its dark tone, pacing, and perceived overstuffing of the storyline with too many characters and plotlines.\n- **Audience Reaction:** Fans had varied responses. While many appreciated seeing iconic superheroes like Batman and Superman share the screen and the introduction of characters like Wonder Woman and the Flash, others felt the film didn't meet their expectations set by previous superhero movies.\n  \n### **Legacy and Impact**\n- Despite the mixed reception, \"Batman v Superman: Dawn of Justice\" played a pivotal role in setting up the **DC Extended Universe (DCEU)**, leading to future films like \"Justice League,\" \"Aquaman,\" and \"Shazam!\".\n- The film also contributed to the eventual reimagining and refinement of DC's cinematic strategy in subsequent releases.\n\n### **Conclusion**\nWhile **\"Batman v Superman: Dawn of Justice\"** didn't become a financial flop and was commercially successful, it faced criticism regarding its narrative and execution. Its legacy is a blend of both achievements in expanding the superhero cinematic landscape and lessons learned for future DC films.\n\nIf you have specific questions about the movie's performance or reception, feel free to ask!",
